# Exemple d'optimalit entre les 3 fct MH, MH_high_dim et MH_high_dim_para sur le modle non lineaire mixte
m <- function(t, phi1, phi2, phi3) (phi1  )/(1+exp((phi2-t)/phi3))
#=======================================#
p <- 4
parameter <- list(sigma2 = .05^2,
                  #rho2 = 5,
                  mu = c(0.9,90,5),
                  omega2 = c(0.005, 40, 1),
                  #S.data data,
                  bara = 90,
                  barb = 30,
                  baralpha = 0.5,
                  beta = rep(0,p))
parameter$beta[1:4] <- c(1,2,-1,-2)*10
#=======================================#
t <- seq(60,120, length.out = 10) #time values
set.seed(123)

G <- 40 ; ng = 4
# link = function(t,phi1, phi2, phi3) phi2#/phi3
link = m

dt <- create_JLS_HD_data(G, ng, t, m, link, parameter)

var.true <- dt$var.true
a <- var.true$a ; var.true$a <- NULL #a fix (et retir des variables latentes)
S.data <- dt$survival
U <- dt$U

Y <- do.call(get_obs, var.true) + rnorm(n, 0, sqrt(parameter$sigma2))
S.data.time <- S.data$obs
S.data.time.log.sum <- sum(log(S.data.time))
model <- SAEM_model( 
  function(sigma2, ...) -n/(2*sigma2),
  function(phi1, phi2, phi3, ...) mean((Y - get_obs(phi1, phi2, phi3) )^2 ), 'sigma2',
  
  # === Variable Latente === #
  latent_vars = list(
    # === Non linear model === #
    latent_variable('phi', dim = G, size = 3, prior = list(mean = 'mu', variance = 'omega2'),
                    add_on = c('zeta(phi1 = phi1, phi2 = phi2, phi3 = phi3, ...)' )),
    
    # === S.data model === #
    latent_variable('b', prior = list(mean = 'barb', variance.hyper = 'sigma2_b'),
                    add_on = c('zeta(b = b, ...) +',
                               'sum(h$eval(b = b, ..., i = c(1,2)))' )),
    latent_variable('alpha', prior = list(mean = 'baralpha', variance.hyper = 'sigma2_alpha'),
                    add_on = c('zeta(alpha = alpha, ...) +',
                               'alpha*h$eval(alpha = alpha,..., i = 3)'))
  ),

  # === Paramtre de regression === #
  regression.parameter = list(
    regression_parameter('beta', 1, function(...) SPGD(30, theta0 = beta,
                                                      step = 0.05, lambda = 1/sqrt(N),
                                                      normalized.grad = T,
                                                      zeta.der.B, N, zeta.B, 
                                                      Z$alpha,  Z$phi1, Z$phi2, Z$phi3,Z$b) )
  )
)
# ---  Initialisation des paramtres --- #
parameter0 <- parameter %>% sapply(function(x) x* runif(1, 1.1,1.4))

parameter0$barb <- 10
parameter0$sigma2 <- 1
parameter0$beta <- runif(p, min = -1, max = 1)
parameter0$baralpha <- 0.1
#===============================================#
load.SAEM(model)
var0 <- init.SAEM(model, 
                  x0 = list(phi = c(1,80,4), 
                            b = parameter0$barb, alpha = parameter0$baralpha), 
                  sd = list(phi = c(.05, 1.5, .5),
                            b = 1, alpha = .1) )
#===================================================================================#
S.tmp <- do.call(S$eval, var.true)
oracle <- maximisation(1, do.call(S$eval, var.true), parameter, var.true)
oracle

saem

exclude.maximisation = c('mu', 'omega2', 'barb','baralpha', 'sigma2')
load.SAEM(model, exclude.maximisation = exclude.maximisation)

parameter0[exclude.maximisation] <- parameter[exclude.maximisation]

res <- SAEM(200, 5, parameter0, var0, Phi, S$eval, maximisation, simulation,
            burnin = 190, 
            adptative.sd = 0.6, verbatim = 3, RDS = params$rds_filename )
